academicProgress: During the reporting period, significant strides were made in strengthening academic and curricular development. Several new programs were launched to align with national priorities and emerging global trends, ensuring that our graduates remain competitive in a rapidly evolving job market. Curriculum reviews were carried out across multiple faculties, focusing on modernizing course content, integrating digital literacy, and embedding research-oriented and practical learning components. Continuous assessments and innovative teaching approaches contributed to a notable improvement in student results and overall academic performance. Faculty development workshops were also conducted to enhance teaching quality and pedagogical innovation.
researchProgress: The institution demonstrated commendable progress in research and innovation this year. A number of research projects were completed, addressing national development challenges and contributing valuable insights to academia and industry. Faculty and students actively participated in national and international conferences, presenting papers and sharing findings that reflect the universityâ€™s growing research capacity. Efforts were made to strengthen research collaborations and establish linkages with external partners. Moreover, initiatives were taken to promote innovation and intellectual property development, resulting in the registration of patents and new prototypes that have practical application potential.
adminProgress: In line with our goal of fostering transparency and efficiency, several administrative and governance reforms were introduced. Updated policies and operational guidelines were implemented to improve institutional management, decision-making, and accountability. The use of digital systems was expanded for record keeping, communication, and data-driven decision processes. Various committees and working groups were formed to ensure participatory governance, streamline processes, and enhance coordination across departments. Administrative staff received capacity-building training to further strengthen institutional governance.
qualityProgress: Continuous quality assurance and enhancement remained a core focus throughout the year. The QAAC (Quality Assurance and Accreditation Committee) activities were intensified, including self-assessment reporting and preparation for external peer reviews. Mechanisms for student and stakeholder feedback were strengthened to inform academic and administrative improvements. Workshops on internal quality culture, learning outcome measurement, and continuous improvement practices were organized. These efforts have collectively contributed to fostering a culture of excellence, accountability, and evidence-based improvement across all levels of operation.
majorChallenges: Despite notable progress, several challenges were encountered during the reporting period. Limited financial resources, delays in administrative processes, and insufficient infrastructure constrained the pace of program implementation. Human resource gaps, especially in technical and research positions, posed difficulties in meeting growing academic demands. Additionally, adapting to rapid technological changes and maintaining digital readiness across faculties required significant effort. Coordination across departments and ensuring consistent policy compliance also remained a concern.
nextYearPlan:
Looking ahead, the institution aims to consolidate achievements and address identified challenges through a well-defined action plan. Key priorities include:

Expanding new academic programs in high-demand and interdisciplinary areas.

Enhancing research capacity through dedicated grants, collaborations, and research labs.

Strengthening e-governance and digital transformation across administrative units.

Advancing quality assurance through continuous monitoring, feedback integration, and capacity development.

Upgrading infrastructure and learning resources to support modern pedagogy.

Fostering partnerships with national and international institutions for academic and research excellence.
